### 4.2 The "Weekly Miracle"

Bach was not just the composer; he was the copyist, rehearsal master, and conductor. He supervised the copying of hundreds of pages of orchestral parts every week, often finishing the ink just hours before the service. Gardiner describes this relentless schedule as a "weekly miracle" of intellectual and spiritual focus.

